# D365 F&O Testing

Microsoft source: [SysTest in Visual Studio](https://learn.microsoft.com/dynamics365/fin-ops-core/dev-itpro/perf-test/testing-support)

## Core rules

- `extends SysTestCase` + `[SysTestMethod]`
- **AutoRollback** (default) — never run on production
- **Data-agnostic** — ATL creates data; no demo dependency
- ATL fluent: `var item = items.default();`
- Names: `when_given_then`

## Scenarios and recommendations

### Unit test new business rule / service method

**Recommend:** `MyPub_ServiceTest extends SysTestCase`; ATL setup; assert outcome; `[SysTestMethod]` per case; `when_given_then` name.

**Avoid:** `test1()`; relying on `US-001` demo customer existing.

### Test expected exception path

**Recommend:** `this.parmExceptionExpected(true);` before call; descriptive method name e.g. `reservingItem_noOnhand_exception`.

**Avoid:** Empty catch swallowing failure.

### Component test across table + class

**Recommend:** ATL navigation/creators/commands; keep test data creation in test method or setup helper.

**Avoid:** Manual `insert()` of dozens of related tables without ATL.

### Pre-check-in gate

**Recommend:** Run SysTest locally; BP zero on changed models; add test for every new public business rule.

**Avoid:** Check-in without test because "hard to set up data".

### Regression after CoC change

**Recommend:** Tests call through public entry point (service or table method) so CoC chain executes.

**Avoid:** Testing private method copy bypassing CoC.

### Performance / load testing

**Recommend:** Separate perf test project; not mixed with unit SysTest suite; use Trace Parser for hotspots.

**Avoid:** Long-running load tests with AutoRollback disabled on shared dev box without coordination.

## SysTest example

```xpp
// BAD
class MyTest { public void test1() { } }

// GOOD
class MyPub_OrderTest extends SysTestCase
{
    [SysTestMethod]
    public void reservingItem_noOnhand_exception()
    {
        var item = items.default().setOnHand(0);
        this.parmExceptionExpected(true);
        MyPub_ReservationService::reserve(item.ItemId, 1);
    }
}
```

